### Creating Connections
Each Connection defines a route from the Source to a specific Destination.
Connections include filter rules that determine which events they handle:
```
const customerConnection = {
name: "chargebee-customer",
source_id: source.id,
destination: {
name: "customer-handler",
type: "CLI",
config: { path: "/webhooks/chargebee/customer" },
},
rules: [
{
type: "filter",
body: {
event_type: { $startsWith: "customer_" },
},
},
],
};
await fetch("https://api.hookdeck.com/2025-07-01/connections", {
method: "PUT",
headers: {
Authorization: `Bearer ${HOOKDECK_API_KEY}`,
"Content-Type": "application/json",
},
body: JSON.stringify(customerConnection),
});
```
The filter rule routes all events where `event_type` starts with `customer_` to this Connection's Destination.
The `type: "CLI"` configuration is for local development with the Hookdeck CLI.
